title: User query: Plan description from client LLM
log: Create a Wayang plan that calculates waiting list totals for each municipality. The plan must filter the waiting list data for the month “2025-05” first. We want two values computed. The total per waiting list type and the overall total for the municipality. The output must be sorted in descending order by the municipality’s total. Output in textfile.

operations.udf: (t: ((Int, String, Int), (Int, String))) => { val wl = t._1; val org = t._2; (org._2, wl._2, wl._3) }
(a: ((String, String), Int), b: ((String, String), Int)) => (a._1, a._2 + b._2)
(t: ((String, (String, Int)), (String, Int))) => { val m = t._1._1; val typ = t._1._2._1; val typeTot = t._1._2._2; val overall = t._2._2; (m, overall, typ, typeTot) }

log.thoughts: Two parallel pipelines compute municipality-level per-type totals and overall totals (both filtered to 2025-05), then join by municipality, sort descending by overall total, and write to text file.

title: Class: PlanMapper Mapped plan finalized for execution

data.table: (SELECT organisation_id, year_month, waiting_list_type, total FROM factwaitinglists) as X
(SELECT organisation_id, municipality FROM organisation) as X

data.udf: (t: ((Int, String, Int), (Int, String))) => { val wl = t._1; val org = t._2; (org._2, wl._2, wl._3) }
(a: ((String, String), Int), b: ((String, String), Int)) => (a._1, a._2 + b._2)

data.table: (SELECT organisation_id, year_month, waiting_list_type, total FROM factwaitinglists) as X

data.udf: (t: ((String, (String, Int)), (String, Int))) => { val m = t._1._1; val typ = t._1._2._1; val typeTot = t._1._2._2; val overall = t._2._2; (m, overall, typ, typeTot) }
